BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 443 Tm (Aura operates under a hybrid participation economy with two primary groups: Citizen) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 429 Tm (Participants and Institutional Participants.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 394 Tm (3. CITIZEN PARTICIPATION MODEL) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 373 Tm (Citizen access remains free. Citizens may read contributions, create identity-bound) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 359 Tm (accounts, publish posts, reply to discourse, and participate in discussion.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 338 Tm (Citizen participation is not monetized directly. Citizens create the discourse environment) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 324 Tm (that generates civic value.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 289 Tm (4. INSTITUTIONAL PARTICIPATION MODEL) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 268 Tm (Institutions represent the primary revenue layer. Institutional accounts provide verified) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 254 Tm (institutional identity, official statement publication, formal correction record) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 240 Tm (infrastructure, document attachments, institutional communication archive, and structured) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 226 Tm (dialogue with citizens.) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 191 Tm (5. INSTITUTIONAL ACCOUNT TIERS) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 170 Tm (Basic Institutional Presence: verified institutional profile, official post capability,) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 156 Tm (correction record system, public dialogue participation. Estimated range: $200 - $500 per) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 61.2 142 Tm (month.) Tj T* ET
